        <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> » <a href="/taxonomy_menu/2">Topic</a> » <a href="/taxonomy_menu/2/95" title="Self-driving cars">Robocars</a></div>        <h1 class="title">Car design changes due to Robocars</h1>
        <div class="tabs"></div>
                          <div class="node">
            <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Mon, 2008-06-23 14:45.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first last taxonomy_term_95"><a href="/topic/robocars" rel="tag" title="The future of computer-driven cars and deliverbots" class="taxonomy_term_95">Robocars</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p><img src=http://www.templetons.com/brad/robocars/aerorider.jpg width=20% class=blogpic>
Robocars will suggest a great number of possible changes in the way we design and market cars.  I now encourage you to read:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><a href="http://www.templetons.com/brad/robocars/design-change.html" title="reference on Automobile design changes due to Robocars" target="_self">Automobile design changes due to Robocars</a></p>
</blockquote>

<p>The big green benefit of robocars comes in large part from the freedom they offer in redesigning the automobile, in particular the ability to specialize automobiles to specific tasks, because they can be so readily hired on demand.  Or to specific fuels in certain areas, or for sleeping, and much more.</p>

<p><br clear=all></p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links inline"><li class="first last blog_usernames_blog"><a href="/blog/brad" title="Read brad&#039;s latest blog entries." class="blog_usernames_blog">brad&#039;s blog</a></li>
</ul></div>  </div>
