</div><a id="comment-13951"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/car-design-changes-due-robocars#comment-13951" class="active">Seniors and healthcare</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Dave Roberts (not verified) on Fri, 2012-09-28 10:17.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Getting to and from medical appointments is a major chore for millions of seniors. It occurs at the precise time in their lives when their driving abilities are failing. The rapid adoption of a limited automated medical taxi system will be a huge boon to both the seniors and other drivers. I can visualize healthcare systems having a fleet of vehicles to pick up patients just in time for their appointments. A slightly larger vehicle could have space for a medical practitioner to take blood pressure readings and other vital signs on the way to the clinic and to dispense advice and care requirements on the return trip. For that matter, a robo-medical-taxi could automate the blood pressure, weight, and other vital signs on the way to the appointment.</p>
</div>
