    <h3 class="title"><a href="/car-design-changes-due-robocars#comment-13964" class="active">Peak Oil consideration</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Allen Knutson (not verified) on Tue, 2012-10-02 14:03.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I imagine that driver wages is a significant fraction of the price of trucking, making it desirable to drive fast (modulo legality and safety issues). Once that's gone, presumably fuel will be the next limiting factor, especially as it gets more expensive. It's more fuel-efficient to go slower. Get ready for a lot of crawling robotrucks, and pressure from trucking companies to lower the minimum speed on highways overnight.</p>
</div>
